    <section class="page">
        <div class="page-number">Page | 19</div>
        <h2>12. Conclusions and Future Directions</h2>
        <h3>12.1 Summary of Findings</h3>
        <p>
            The FlashIn Delivery project successfully demonstrates a working
            last-mile delivery management system. It provides clear modules for
            centers, drivers, orders, and routes. The dashboard gives useful summary
            information, and the professional interface makes the website suitable for
            academic presentation.
        </p>
        <p>
            The project proves that even a small web application can improve visibility
            in delivery operations. By using a centralized dashboard and CRUD modules,
            a business can avoid scattered records and track its operational flow more
            clearly. The project also shows the importance of structured database
            relationships because orders, routes, centers, and drivers depend on each
            other in real-world delivery management.
        </p>
        <h3>12.2 Recommendations for Enhancements</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Add user authentication and role-based access for administrators and dispatchers.</li>
            <li>Add automated route optimization using distance matrix APIs.</li>
            <li>Add live map tracking for drivers and orders.</li>
            <li>Add customer-side order tracking with order status updates.</li>
            <li>Add delivery reports, charts, and exportable analytics.</li>
            <li>Add payment status and invoice generation.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>12.3 Future Scope of the Website</h3>
        <p>
            In the future, FlashIn can be expanded into a complete logistics platform.
            Mobile apps can be added for drivers and customers. Real-time location
            sharing, optimized multi-stop routing, notification systems, and advanced
            analytics can make the system more powerful and industry-ready.
        </p>
    </section>

